  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Healing Hands of Joy - Women&apos;s health</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HHOJ began a pilot project in Mekelle, the capital of the Tigray region, in 2010. Here, the rate of fistula is the highest in Ethiopia and one of the highest in the world. Committed to working with existing health networks, the organisation formed a local Steering Committee comprised of government and non-government organisations.  HHOJ&#x2019;s approach has three main strands: prevention (increasing skilled, facility-based delivery and educating pregnant women), reintegration (to empower fistula survivors to educate women in their communities) and identification (to identify old or new cases of fistula for treatment, referring patients to Hamlin Fistula for treatment and then inviting them to join the HHOJ Safe Motherhood Ambassador programme).</narrative>
  </description>
